Veteran Kenyan politician Kenneth Matiba died Sunday evening at the age of 85 years. Matiba, who was on the forefront of fighting for Kenya’s second liberation, died while undergoing treatment at the Karen Hospital ICU in Nairobi after suffering from cardiac arrest.  Matiba’s medical woes can be traced back to his 1990 dentation where he was denied access to medical treatment – this according to his physician, Dr Dan Gikonyo.  Today on The Untold Story we tell the story of the Catastrophic Detention of Kenneth Matiba. Watch Part II here. 